The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 March is 227,026 (26,166.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 February, there were 4,365 new confirmed cases (503.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 February, there were 6,472 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (2,107 fewer cases).
